post_text:
BHS students in the Business Management Program who previously qualified for the Business Professionals of America State Conference recently competed virtually to earn state honors.

The results are in!

Senior Ethan Wise placed FIRST in Payroll Accounting;
Senior Elizabeth Stedman placed FIRST in Fundamental Word Processing;
Senior Alex Klein placed FOURTH in Intermediate Word Processing;
Junior Jayanah Sutton placed FIFTH in Legal Office Procedures;
Junior Jakob Denee placed SEVENTH in Fundamental Accounting.

Students placing in the top five would normally advance to the National Conference which unfortunately has been cancelled. We're proud of our students who rise up and accept challenges regardless of the obstacles they face. #PurplePride

